        "body": "## Summary\n- Add bundled `sms` channel support with Twilio inbound webhooks, signed request validation, pairing/allowlist access, and outbound text replies.\n- Wire account resolution, env-only defaults, named `defaultAccount`, route-session keys, replay dedupe, chunked outbound delivery, config metadata, docs, labels, and plugin inventory reference docs.\n- Preserve shared pairing account context so approval notifications can use the correct channel account.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/sms src/channels/plugins/pairing.ts src/cli/pairing-cli.ts`\n- `pnpm exec tsgo -p extensions/sms/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-vitest-sms-config node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/sms/src/phone.test.ts extensions/sms/src/accounts.test.ts extensions/sms/src/twilio.test.ts extensions/sms/src/inbound.test.ts extensions/sms/src/gateway.test.ts extensions/sms/src/channel.test.ts extensions/sms/src/send.test.ts extensions/sms/src/webhook.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm plugins:inventory:check`\n- `pnpm config:channels:check`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `autoreview --mode local` clean\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: OpenClaw now exposes a standalone Twilio-backed SMS channel with signed inbound webhooks, pairing/allowlist access, outbound replies, chunking, config metadata, labels, and docs.\nReal environment tested: Local source checkout on macOS, Node/pnpm repo toolchain.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Commands listed in Verification above, plus GitHub label creation for `channel: sms`.\nEvidence after fix: Focused SMS Vitest shard passed 8 files / 21 tests; full build completed successfully; generated plugin inventory and bundled channel config metadata checks passed; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: Unknown SMS senders in pairing mode receive a pairing challenge, allowed senders route through the canonical session key, duplicate webhook paths and replayed message SIDs are rejected, signed form values are preserved for Twilio verification, env-only configuration starts the default account, and long replies are chunked before Twilio sends.\nWhat was not tested: Live Twilio webhook delivery against a real Twilio phone number.\n",
